## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend

- Tech stack alignment:
  - React with TypeScript
  - State management via React context or lightweight store
  - Styling via CSS-in-JS (e.g., styled-components, emotion) or CSS Modules per project standards
  - Use existing design system tokens for colors, typography, spacing
- Components:
  - Implement all components listed above with proper props typing
  - Ensure robust null-safety in all data usage
  - Initialize state to safe defaults:
    - useState<ReportSection[]>([]) for arrays
    - useState<AnalysisProgress[]>([]) for progress items
    - useState<string>("") for text fields where applicable
- Data handling:
  - All API results must be guarded: const report = data ?? null; const items = Array.isArray(report?.sections) ? report.sections : []
  - Use optional chaining where needed
  - Validate shapes: const sections = Array.isArray(response?.sections) ? response.sections : []
- Accessibility:
  - Semantic HTML (aria-labels, roles)
  - Keyboard navigable modals and controls
  - Proper heading order (H1 for page title, H2/H3 for sections)
- Interaction design:
  - Smooth micro-interactions (150–220ms)
  - Hover/focus states per design system
  - Confident but forgiving error handling with user-friendly messages
- Data visualization:
  - Minimalist charts using SVG or lightweight charting library
  - Teal gradient bars from #2FD7BC to #14B9A0
  - No dense gridlines; faint baselines
- API integration:
  - All API calls must be standard fetch/axios with error handling
  - Use a shared APIErrorBoundary or toast approach for user feedback
- Security:
  - Token handling and authenticated requests via Supabase session
  - Ensure user-scoped data access

### Backend

- APIs to support the frontend for the Analysis Landing:
  - GET /api/reports?search=&status=&date=&tags= (Search & Filter Reports)
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId (Fetch report)
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/gtm (GTM synthesis results)
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/perplexity (Market evidence)
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/anthropic (Repo interpretation)
  - POST /api/reports/:reportId/draft (Save customized report draft)
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/export?format=pdf|docx (Export)
- Data models:
  - Report: id, userId, title, executiveSummary, maturityScore, useCase, evidenceLinks, etc.
  - Evidence: id, source, snippet, confidence, citation
  - Competitor: name, snippet, source
  - ICP: segments, personas, rationale
  - Positioning: statement, differentiators, proofPoints
  - Pricing: observedExamples, recommendedRange
  - RoadmapItem: id, title, description, priority, effort, impact
  - Progress: stage, percent
- Safety:
  - Validate all inputs; guard against null/undefined in all responses
  - Normalize API responses to expected shapes before consumption

### Integration

- Data flow:
  - Frontend fetches report data and progress data
  - GTM synthesis pulls from Anthropic (repo interpretation) and Perplexity (market evidence)
  - The synthesized GTM report is composed from these sources and surfaced on Analysis Landing
  - Report Viewer/Editor allows user edits saved back to the server as a draft
- State orchestration:
  - Use a central data store or React context to surface current report, progress, and evidence
  - Ensure data integrity with defensive checks and default fallbacks
- Security:
  - All API calls require user authentication
  - Ensure proper authorization: users can only access their own reports

