## User Experience Flow

1) User lands on Analysis Results (Report Landing)
- If no report selected, show a list with Search & Filter, and a prominent CTA to create or open a report
- Show Analysis Progress strip summarizing pipeline statuses (ingestion, heuristics, Anthropic, Perplexity)

2) Explore high-level GTM output
- Executive Summary: read-only but with an Edit option
- Competitor Snapshot: expand each competitor for more details, click-through citations
- ICP Section: view segments/personas; add notes if needed
- Positioning & Differentiators: view suggested statements and proof points
- Pricing Panel: view patterns and recommended ranges
- Messaging Angles: quick copy suggestions

3) Evidence & Citations
- Expandable Evidence Panel with ability to annotate and filter by source

4) Next Steps and Roadmap
- View prioritized actions; reorder if necessary; mark as planned/done
- Hover details show ETA and impact

5) Analysis Progress
- See live ingestion progress and current analysis stages

6) Report Viewer / Editor
- Switch to Editor mode
- Edit messaging blocks, annotate evidence, accept/reject recommendations
- Save as Draft; export to PDF/Docx; share or schedule monitoring

7) Actions
- Use the Actions Toolbar to customize, export, or share the report
- Access governance of the report (permissions) as needed

