## Technical Specifications

- Data Models (Schema details)
  - reports
    - id: string
    - userId: string
    - title: string
    - executiveSummary: string
    - maturityScore: number
    - useCase: string
    - createdAt: timestamp
    - updatedAt: timestamp
  - evidence
    - id: string
    - reportId: string
    - source: string
    - snippet: string
    - confidence: number
    - citation: string
  - competitors (embedded in report)
    - name: string
    - snippet: string
    - source: string
  - icp
    - segments: array of { id, name, rationale }
    - personas: array of { id, name, description }
  - positioning
    - statement: string
    - differentiators: array<string>
    - proofPoints: array<string>
  - pricing
    - observedExamples: array<string>
    - recommendedRange: string
  - roadmap
    - items: array of { id, title, description, priority, effort, impact, status }
  - progress
    - stages: array of { id, name, percent }

- API Endpoints
  - GET /api/reports?search=&status=&date=&tags=
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/gtm
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/perplexity
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/anthropic
  - POST /api/reports/:reportId/draft
  - GET /api/reports/:reportId/export?format=pdf|docx

- Security
  - Supabase auth session management
  - Protected routes; verify userId matches session
  - Validate and sanitize all inputs; server-side guards

- Validation
  - Ensure response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Always coalesce: const items = data ?? []
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

