# Analysis Results (Report Landing) — Comprehensive AI Development Prompt

This prompt is intended for an AI development tool to build the Analysis Results (Report Landing) feature set with strict runtime safety, a polished UI/UX, and robust frontend/backend integration. It enforces the mandatory runtime safety rules described in the PROJECT CONTEXT (null checks, use of data ?? [], Array.isArray guards, proper useState([]), etc.). It covers page description, components, data flows, APIs, integration points, and acceptance criteria.

---

## Analysis Results (Report Landing)

## Overview
Develop an Analysis Results (Report Landing) page that presents a synthesized GTM plan from repo-derived signals and live market research. The page should function as the primary report overview with executive summary, evidence-backed claims, competitor snapshot, ICP/audience signals, pricing guidance, messaging angles, and a prioritized next-steps roadmap. It must integrate seamlessly with Search & Filter Reports, GTM Synthesis & Report Generation, Market Research (Perplexity), and Repository Understanding (Anthropic LLM). It should also support an Analysis Progress view and a Report Viewer/Editor for editing, annotating evidence, and exporting customized reports.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)

What this page is:
- A cohesive landing/dashboard for an Analysis Results report, presenting a synthesized GTM plan with clearly labeled sections:
  - Executive Summary
  - Evidence-backed Claims (with citations)
  - Competitor Snapshot (top 5 with evidence snippets and sources)
  - ICP/Audience Signals (segments & personas)
  - Positioning & Differentiators
  - Pricing Guidance & Patterns
  - Messaging Angles (tonality, value propositions)
  - Prioritized Next Steps (roadmap with effort/impact)
  - Evidence Panel (raw citations and repo snippets with confidence)
  - Actions Toolbar (customize, download/export, share, schedule monitoring)
- Connected features:
  - Search & Filter Reports: navigate and filter multiple analyses by status, date, tags
  - GTM Synthesis & Report Generation: auto-synthesize from repository signals + market research
  - Market Research (Perplexity): live market evidence, citations
  - Repository Understanding (Anthropic LLM): repo interpretation, target users, problems, core flows, maturity, confidence
  - Analysis Progress: visualizes ingestion & analysis pipeline
  - Report Viewer/Editor: edit messaging, annotate evidence, accept/reject recommendations, save/export

UI elements and how they should look:
- Executive Summary Card
  - One-paragraph product description
  - Maturity score (visual badge)
  - Primary use-case bullet
  - Quick action to “Edit Summary”
- Competitor Snapshot
  - Top 5 competitors
  - Short evidence snippets per competitor
  - Source links (Perplexity citations)
- Audience & ICP Section
  - Segments, Personas, and Rationale (from repo signals)
- Positioning & Differentiators Block
  - Positioning statements
  - Key differentiators with proof points
- Pricing Patterns
  - Observed pricing in category
  - Examples and recommended pricing range
- Next-Step Roadmap
  - Prioritized actions with estimated effort and impact
- Evidence Panel
  - Raw citations from Perplexity
  - Repository snippets with confidence scores
- Actions Toolbar
  - Customize Report, Download/Export, Share, Schedule Monitoring
- Layout & Visuals
  - Card-based modular sections with subtle shadows
  - Clean typography, generous whitespace
  - Data visuals (where applicable) with teal accents and gradient metrics
  - Global navigation and an inline search bar for quick access
- Interactions
  - Hover/focus states follow the Design System
  - Expansion panels for Evidence items
  - Inline annotate/review controls in Report Viewer/Editor

UI/UX Guidelines:
- The page should be scannable, with a strong typographic hierarchy and signposting sections
- Evidence and citations must be clearly differentiated from conclusions
- All interactive elements should have accessible labels and keyboard navigation
- Use the project’s Design System exactly as described (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, and micro-interactions)
- All charts (where used) follow the minimalist teal gradient style

API Integrations:
- No external API endpoints are hard-coded in this prompt; the page must wire into existing backend endpoints for:
  - Fetching a report by ID or the current user’s selected analysis
  - Searching & filtering reports
  - Retrieving GTM synthesis results
  - Retrieving Perplexity market evidence (citations, competitor lists, pricing examples)
  - Retrieving Anthropic repository interpretation (product description, target users, problems, maturity, confidence)
  - Saving customized report edits
  - Exporting/downloading reports (PDF/Docs)
- All API interactions must guard against null/undefined values and conform to the runtime safety requirements.

