- [ ] The Analysis Landing page renders executive summary, evidence, competitors, ICP, positioning, pricing, messaging, and roadmap sections with proper typography, spacing, and teal accent usage as defined.
- [ ] All frontend data access uses null-safe patterns: (data ?? []), Array.isArray() guards, and useState([]) defaults for arrays; all API responses are validated to expected shapes.
- [ ] The Search & Filter Reports component correctly filters reports by status, date, and tags, with results updating in real-time.
- [ ] The GTM Synthesis section presents a structured report with sections: exec summary, competitors, ICP, positioning, pricing, messaging angles, and prioritized next steps; data sources (Anthropic/Perplexity) are visible as citations.
- [ ] The Evidence Panel shows raw citations with confidence scores and source links; items expand/collapse without errors.
- [ ] The Report Viewer/Editor allows editing messaging, annotating evidence, accepting/rejecting recommendations, and saving as a draft; exports generate a valid PDF/Docx file.
- [ ] Analysis Progress view accurately represents ingestion, static heuristics, Anthropic analysis, and Perplexity research progress with progress bars.
- [ ] All API endpoints return properly shaped data; error states are user-friendly and non-crashing.
- [ ] UI components adhere to the provided Visual Style, Color Palette, Typography, and Layout guidelines.

---

## UI/UX Guidelines

Apply the project's design system precisely:
- Color Palette, Typography, Spacing, Shadows, and Micro-interactions as described
- Card design (rounded corners 14–18px), 1px border #E6E9EE, subtle drop shadow
- Primary CTA: #111827 with white text, rounded full
- Accent teal (#21C7A7) and pale aqua (#E7FAF6) usage in headings, highlights, badges
- Teal gradient for success/analytics bars: #2FD7BC → #14B9A0
- Focus rings on inputs: rgba(33,199,167,0.18)
- Responsive behavior: feature grid with 3 cards per row on desktop, collapses to single column on narrow viewports
- Accessibility: aria labels, keyboard navigable, readable color contrast per WCAG

---

## Visual Style (Repeatable Requirements)

- Color, typography, and layout tokens are defined in the Visual Style block and must be used consistently
- Cards, spacing, and grids mirror the described 8/16/24 spacing system
- Data visuals emphasize clarity and trust; avoid clutter
- All interactive elements follow the hover/focus guidelines

---

## Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: Apply these rules in all generated code.

1) Supabase query results:
   - const items = data ?? []
2) Array methods safety:
   - (items ?? []).map(...) OR Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
3) React useState defaults:
   - useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays
4) API response shapes:
   - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
5) Optional chaining:
   - Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing nested data
6) Destructuring with defaults:
   - const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

---

## Final Deliverables

- Frontend code:
  - TypeScript React components implementing AnalysisLandingPage, subcomponents, API client, and ui styling per design system
  - Proper null-safety patterns in all data access
  - Accessibility-compliant markup
- Backend code (or API contracts if backend is external):
  - API routes with validation and error handling
  - Data models and schema definitions
- Documentation:
  - Developer notes on data flow, component interfaces, and integration points
  - How to extend with additional markets or new signals

